Contrary to the first type of\ncorrections, it appears at open string tree-level and shifts the definition of\nthe K\\\"ahler coordinates in terms of the classical volume but leaves the volume\nitself uncorrected. Our work has implications for moduli stabilization and\nmodel building and suggests interesting generalizations to F-theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Jun 2014 20:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 19 Aug 2014 09:10:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 26 Feb 2015 12:10:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-27"}
