sized\nuncertainty of the convective Urca process in our hybrid WD models of SN Ia\nprogenitors, we consider a number of their potentially possible alternative\ninstances for different mixing assumptions, all of which reach a phase of\nexplosive C ignition, either off or in the centre. Our hybrid SN Ia progenitor\nmodels have much lower C to O abundance ratios at the moment of the explosive C\nignition than their pure CO counterparts, which may explain the observed\ndiversity of the SNe Ia.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Jul 2014 14:16:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Dec 2014 19:55:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
